      "writtenOn": "2017-09-25T12:39:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For the constexpr versions of these functions, we can probably just have the methods take uint8_t.  The static asserts are fine but probably redundant.  The compiler will let us know if we pass too large a value, e.g.\n\n  constexpr static uint8_t foo(uint8_t n) { return ...; }\n  ...\n  printf(\"%d\\n\", foo(256));\n\n  warning: implicit conversion from \u0027int\u0027 to \u0027uint8_t\u0027 (aka \u0027unsigned char\u0027) changes\n      value from 256 to 0 [-Wconstant-conversion]",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "7ee4dacf98344adb42d5362dc33252d1147b181b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
